      "title": "Development of a software complex for the diagnosis of dentoalveolar anomalies using neural networks",
      "tldr": "This paper presents a software complex for diagnosing dentoalveolar anomalies using convolutional neural networks to automate teleradiographic image analysis, addressing the need for efficient and accurate diagnosis in orthodontics; the approach involves integrating neural networks into a treatment planning system, contributing a tool that reduces manual effort and medical errors; findings show improved diagnostic efficiency through automated image decoding, with implications for enhancing clinical practice and reducing workload in orthodontic care.",
      "abstract": "This article describes the goals and objectives of developing a software complex for planning the treatment of dentoalveolar anomalies, the architecture of the software complex as interacting components for treatment planning, as well as the principle of using algorithms using convolutional neural networks within the software complex for a component that solves the problem of decoding a teleradiographic image.",
